<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77eb320e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460vv–16"><num value="460vv–16">§ 460vv–16.</num><heading> Fishing and wildlife</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter shall be construed as affecting the jurisdiction or responsibilities of the State with respect to wildlife and fish in the areas designated by this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77eb320f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/499/s18">Pub. L. 100–499, § 18</ref>, <date date="1988-10-18">Oct. 18, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/2499">102 Stat. 2499</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
